26/04/2004
WASHINGTON, United States -- The World Bank announced on Sunday (25 April) that Turkey is among eleven countries displaying exemplary implementation of projects sponsored by the Bank. 
Turkey won recognition for its Basic Education Programme, aimed at reducing poverty by providing high quality educational opportunities to more of its citizens. 
Project results will be presented at a conference in Shanghai late next month. 
(Anadolu Agency, TRT 2 - 25/04/04)
